THE SECOND THREE FIRES: Post-Riften Adventure Structures (Gate 3)

Campaign Context: Act III, immediately following Riften (Esbern recruited, Mila taken in,
Kyboh gone, the Jagged Crown desecrated, Davinia carrying the amulet Ismara won't let her
deliver). The party is at the Bee and Barb when three couriers arrive across three days.
Each represents a different genre, challenge type, and consequence track - the same triage
structure as Korvanjund's "Crown" gate and the first "Three Fires," now at higher stakes
and with the party's own sins folded into the crisis.

The Unchosen Consequences Rule: The fires the party does NOT choose escalate off-screen,
delivering their consequences in future sessions as rumors, refugees, dead allies, and
direct confrontations. They cannot put out all three. The campaign-defining cruelty of
this gate: one fire is a disaster THEY made (Windhelm), one is the world ending by inches
(the Throat), and one is the only thing that turns them from reactive to strategic (Bleak
Falls). Saving people vs. winning the war vs. owning the guilt.

THE FRAMING TENSION: Bjorn has just promised Davinia "we're going to get him back" -
meaning Kyboh. The party wants to chase north after their friend. The world will not let
them. None of the three fires is Kyboh. (And Kyboh cannot be recovered - see the Kyboh /
Hjolmar villain doc. The party does not know this yet. Let the pull north be real and
let the triage deny it.)

