FIRE A: THE BARRICADES OF WINDHELM
Location: Windhelm (the Gray Quarter, the Palace of the Kings, the sealed walls, the
  Afflicted Conclave's hidden Peryite shrine)
Villain: Alfonso's own plague (now an uncontrolled epidemic) + Antoine of Forelhost
  (Dragon Cult alchemist, harvesting and refining it into Strain 2.0). Vokun looms in the
  background - he watched Dawnstar dismantle the First Cohort and let the plague do his work.
Theme: Reckoning / Medical Horror / Theological Crisis
Conflict Type: Containment under siege / Investigation / Moral confrontation

The Courier: A feverish young Stormcloak, sent by Galmar. The Korvanjund medical supplies
the Lanterns left behind went north with the First Cohort as proof of alliance - and were
laced, in the dark, by Alfonso's hands, with deliberate intent. Half the Cohort died in
the snow before Dawnstar's walls. The plague followed the retreat home. Windhelm is sealed.
Ulfric is behind closed doors. Galmar holds the barricades alone and begs Davinia "if you
have any honor left." The disease weaponises its own cure: restoration magic makes it
spread faster. The army is dying of exactly what the party made it die of.

Major Character Beats
- Alfonso: This is his reckoning and his opportunity. The epidemic is his masterpiece
  running unsupervised. Antoine is here harvesting it for Strain 2.0 (the theft Alfonso has
  been racing). And the Afflicted Conclave - the Peryite purists whose hidden archive holds
  the soul-vessel scripture that might stabilise his rusting phylactery - is in this city.
  The cure he could offer Windhelm and the cure he needs for himself route through the same
  doctrine. Saving the army means weaponising his own plague-craft to UNMAKE a plague, in
  front of the people it's killing.
- Davinia: The lie comes due. Galmar trusts her because she deceived him about the Crown
  and he believed it. Now he's begging her to fix a disaster her own party authored.
  Whether she tells him the truth, fixes it silently, or lets him keep believing she's a
  savior defines the rest of the Stormcloak relationship - and her.
- Orion: The Gray Quarter and the sealed city are perfect cover and perfect trap. Varon's
  pressure (the Hroki/Windhelm contract, the question of whether Orion can kill cleanly in
  a fortress) lives here. So does Valerius's leash.

Section Structure
Section 1 (The Sealed Gate - Social/Triage): Windhelm's walls are closed; the dying are
  outside in refugee camps, the living are quarantined within. The party must get in past
  a city that doesn't want to be breached, and immediately triage who can be saved.
Section 2 (Galmar's Barricade - The Reunion): Galmar, exhausted, holding the inner line.
  The reunion with "Uncle Galmar" against the backdrop of his army rotting from the inside.
  The investigation begins: where is the plague concentrating, and why is healing making
  it worse?
Section 3 (The Gray Quarter - The Conclave): The trail leads to the Afflicted Conclave's
  hidden Peryite shrine. The schism (Purists/Pragmatists/Visionaries) confronts Alfonso -
  living messiah in a desecrated Crown. He must win the scripture that is both Windhelm's
  cure and his own.
Section 4 (Antoine's Cell - The Rival): Antoine's infiltrators are sampling the strain.
  Confrontation with the rival alchemist (or his proxies); the Strain 2.0 stakes; he will
  almost certainly escape to Rahgot, but the party can deny him the refined sample.
Section 5 (The Cure / The Choice): Synthesising and deploying the counter-agent across a
  dying city. Whether Galmar learns the truth. Whether Alfonso claims the doctrine.

The Reward: The Peryite soul-vessel scripture (Alfonso's lead on stabilising the
  phylactery - see The Rusting Phylactery, Section VII). Galmar's continued trust OR a
  cleansing confession. A foothold in Windhelm. The Forelhost Strain 2.0 sample if Antoine
  is denied.
The Consequence (If Ignored): Windhelm falls to the plague. Galmar dies on the barricades.
  The Stormcloak cause collapses from its heart outward; the Civil War tips. Antoine
  perfects Strain 2.0 and delivers it to Rahgot. Davinia's chance to make the lie right
  dies with Galmar. Dragon Cult Clock advances.

