THE PERSONAL PATH (THE FOURTH OPTION): GOING NORTH

As with the first Three Fires, there is a fourth choice - ignore all three crises and chase
the party's own wounds. Here that means going north after Kyboh (Bjorn's promise), or to
Solitude for Davinia's father / Valerius, or to the Singing Glacier on Kyboh's trail.

The Cruelty: Kyboh cannot be saved (he is dead; the body belongs to Hjolmar now, and the
Echo is a copy - see the Kyboh/Hjolmar doc). The party does not know this. If they choose
the Personal Path, they spend the gate chasing a friend who no longer exists while Windhelm
burns, the Throat is corrupted, and the Dragonstone is lost. The most emotionally honest
choice is the most catastrophic one. Handle the eventual reveal with care.

