GM NOTES: RUNNING THE SECOND THREE FIRES

The Three Truths of This Gate
- Windhelm is the fire they LIT. The horror is ownership. Alfonso made this; Davinia lied
  her way into Galmar's trust. Don't let them save it cleanly.
- The Throat is the fire that ENDS THE WORLD. Highest cosmic stakes, lowest personal
  connection - which is exactly why it's tempting to defer. Make Saijah feel it so the
  table can't fully ignore it.
- The Dragonstone is the fire that WINS. It's cold and unglamorous and it's the only one
  that buys them initiative. The party that always chooses the human emergency will stay
  reactive until Act IV crushes them.

Unchosen Consequences Delivery
- Session after the choice: rumors and refugees from the two ignored fires. NPCs react.
- Two sessions later: direct consequences land (Galmar's death notice / a corrupted-time
  refugee from the mountain / a Dragon Cult courier gloating over the lost Dragonstone).
- Long-term: the ignored fires become Act IV problems, and the relevant clock (Dragon Cult,
  Dagon, Civil War) advances per its own document.

Pacing
- Each fire is ~2 sessions (Prologue + Sections 1-2, then Sections 3-5). The Dragonstone
  delve can run shorter (1-1.5) - it's the "clean" option by design.

Character Arc Integration
- Alfonso: Windhelm is his reckoning AND his phylactery cure-lead (the Conclave scripture).
- Saijah: the Bleeding Stair is her Dagon-hunt payoff and her Kynareth/Hircine crossroads.
- Davinia: Windhelm is where the Galmar lie comes due.
- Bjorn: the Throat and Bleak Falls both press the Dragonborn question; the Personal Path
  is his grief talking.
- Orion: Windhelm holds the Hroki contract and Varon's competence test.

The Weight of Choice
The core theme remains triage - but escalated. The party cannot save everyone, and this
time one of the fires is a mirror. They will choose which to fight and they will live with
the others burning. Make every consequence land. Make the pull north (Kyboh) real, and make
the world refuse it.
